00:45.165 --> 00:48.536
<i>( wind whistling )</i>

01:09.622 --> 01:11.925
( creaking )

01:18.566 --> 01:20.635
<i>( dog barking in distance )</i>

01:24.037 --> 01:25.774
( giggling )

01:51.231 --> 01:53.434
I'm sorry.

01:55.236 --> 02:00.639
I don't know... well, I can't even
remember what got it started, babe.

02:00.641 --> 02:03.077
You're too stubborn, Carter.

02:06.814 --> 02:08.949
- ( barking )
- ( giggling )

02:10.250 --> 02:13.455
Sam, slow down! Watch where you're going.

02:18.191 --> 02:20.160
You said you were gonna
clean up that field.

02:22.563 --> 02:23.898
( sighs )

02:52.792 --> 02:55.529
<i>( crickets chirping )</i>

03:04.804 --> 03:06.771
...and so we remember Crayton

03:06.773 --> 03:09.074
for what he accomplished for his family.

03:09.076 --> 03:10.979
<i>A gift that we will treasure.</i>

03:13.713 --> 03:15.080
( camera shutter clicks )

03:15.082 --> 03:17.148
You told Aunt Jane you quit.

03:17.150 --> 03:20.051
Yeah, well, I gave up half
my day to drive you up here,

03:20.053 --> 03:21.920
so let's call it a truce

03:21.922 --> 03:23.921
and go wish your parents a
happy anniversary, okay, Bird?

03:23.923 --> 03:25.991
Don't call me that.

03:25.993 --> 03:29.093
( sighs ) Okay, Isabelle.

03:29.095 --> 03:32.065
Look, why don't we pay
our respects real quick?

03:34.134 --> 03:35.769
I don't want you to come.

03:37.004 --> 03:38.370
Fine,

03:38.372 --> 03:40.808
but leave the camera here with me, okay?

03:42.743 --> 03:45.943
You know, you can't hide
behind that thing forever.

03:45.945 --> 03:48.847
( sighs ) Okay.

03:48.849 --> 03:52.050
Just don't take any
pictures of the service.

03:52.052 --> 03:53.721
Okay.

03:56.189 --> 03:57.324
Here you go.

04:00.026 --> 04:02.129
I'll be right here.

04:04.631 --> 04:07.334
I'm serious about not
taking any pictures, Bird.

04:08.701 --> 04:10.704
Isabelle!

04:27.954 --> 04:29.356
( camera shutter clicks )

04:31.958 --> 04:34.425
Hi.

04:34.427 --> 04:37.230
I've been taking real
good care of your camera.

04:41.335 --> 04:43.204
I...

04:45.271 --> 04:46.937
( camera shutter clicks )

04:46.939 --> 04:49.677
Priest: <i>...and so we remember him...</i>

05:13.199 --> 05:15.266
...in that case,

05:15.268 --> 05:17.002
may we leave here

05:17.004 --> 05:20.471
with but one overarching thought

05:20.473 --> 05:22.206
in our minds...

05:22.208 --> 05:25.110
that Crayton will always...

05:25.112 --> 05:26.877
<i>( gunshot )</i>

05:26.879 --> 05:28.649
Father?

05:34.287 --> 05:36.324
- <i>( gunshot )</i>
- ( screams )

05:48.299 --> 05:48.867
Oh, my God.

05:48.869 --> 05:51.071
Please. Please!

05:52.872 --> 05:54.973
- ( gunshot )
- ( screams ) Okay!

05:54.975 --> 05:56.841
Okay. Please.

05:56.843 --> 06:00.011
I understand it's... it's over,

06:00.013 --> 06:02.514
<i>but... please...</i>

06:02.516 --> 06:04.983
<i>I'm asking you, we
can talk about this.</i>

06:04.985 --> 06:06.817
<i>We can sit down, we can
make some kind of a deal,</i>

06:06.819 --> 06:08.819
<i>just, I'm begging you. I'm
begging you to please...</i>

06:08.821 --> 06:10.824
- <i>just don't...</i>
- Shh.

06:17.797 --> 06:19.434
Take a good look.

06:21.268 --> 06:24.802
- You only get one.
- ( camera shutter clicks )

06:24.804 --> 06:27.172
- I don't know you.
- But you know my employer.

06:27.174 --> 06:30.175
You know you don't challenge
a man in his position.

06:30.177 --> 06:32.480
- Please.
- I've shown you my face.

06:33.881 --> 06:35.913
So you're already dead.

06:35.915 --> 06:38.083
- ( gunshot )
- ( gasps, thuds )

06:38.085 --> 06:40.354
( whimpers, gasps )

06:44.223 --> 06:46.159
( gunshot )

06:50.297 --> 06:52.166
( whistles )

07:12.485 --> 07:13.985
( camera shutter clicks )

07:13.987 --> 07:15.823
( grunts )

07:29.136 --> 07:30.905
( panting )

07:34.508 --> 07:36.244
Don't forget your book.

07:57.997 --> 08:00.233
( panting ) Roger.

08:07.506 --> 08:10.040
Roger: <i>Isabelle!</i>

08:10.042 --> 08:13.278
- Isabelle!
- Can I help you?

08:13.280 --> 08:15.916
Yeah, I'm looking for a
little girl in a red dress.

08:19.118 --> 08:20.885
Oh.

08:20.887 --> 08:22.419
There's the little angel right now.

08:22.421 --> 08:25.222
Roger! No!

08:25.224 --> 08:27.993
( gunshot )

08:27.995 --> 08:29.497
Roger!

08:33.567 --> 08:34.467
( gunshot )

08:39.438 --> 08:41.275
( cawing )

08:55.389 --> 08:59.126
<i>( clanging )</i>

10:09.295 --> 10:12.032
Bird: <i>Help! Help me!</i>

10:13.132 --> 10:14.599
<i>Help!</i>

10:14.601 --> 10:17.134
<i>Help me, please!</i>

10:17.136 --> 10:19.372
Someone help, please!

10:20.473 --> 10:22.275
<i>Help!</i>

10:24.044 --> 10:26.043
Help!

10:26.045 --> 10:27.177
Hey.

10:27.179 --> 10:29.014
Whoa, whoa, whoa, hey, hey, hey.

10:29.016 --> 10:30.648
It's okay, it's okay. I can help you.

10:30.650 --> 10:33.183
What happened? Tell me what happened.

10:33.185 --> 10:35.422
- Is somebody hurt?
- ( gunshot )

10:45.131 --> 10:47.468
- ( gunshot )
- <i>( Isabelle screams )</i>

11:04.550 --> 11:05.987
( gunshot )

11:13.593 --> 11:16.494
( grunting )

11:16.496 --> 11:19.066
( pants )

11:29.675 --> 11:31.743
Oh, fuck.

11:31.745 --> 11:34.312
Fuck.

11:34.314 --> 11:36.480
Hey, you took some buckshot, did ya?

11:36.482 --> 11:37.617
( gunshots )

11:46.193 --> 11:48.629
( whispering ) Psst! Get back. Get back!

12:13.285 --> 12:16.321
- ( gunshot )
- Give it up, mister!

12:16.323 --> 12:17.721
You ain't getting through to me!

12:17.723 --> 12:20.191
Just making sure

12:20.193 --> 12:21.658
- you know your place.
- ( gunshot )

12:21.660 --> 12:24.562
My place? Where's that, huh?

12:24.564 --> 12:26.563
I'm sitting pretty on the high ground

12:26.565 --> 12:29.134
while you waste your clip
burying bullets in the furniture.

12:29.136 --> 12:31.870
<i>That .45 ain't gonna cut a hole
through me and you know it.</i>

12:31.872 --> 12:33.871
<i>Not with that fucking
condom it's wearing.</i>

12:33.873 --> 12:35.308
Well, well, well.

12:37.577 --> 12:39.580
<i>The man knows his guns.</i>

12:46.352 --> 12:48.088
But so do I.

12:58.598 --> 13:00.133
<i>( groans )</i>

13:07.339 --> 13:09.506
( chuckles )

13:09.508 --> 13:11.543
Pitiful range you got

13:11.545 --> 13:14.512
with that candy-ass 20
gauge you're riding up there.

13:14.514 --> 13:18.182
You ain't nothing but a quail hunter, boy.

13:18.184 --> 13:20.621
<i>And I damn sure ain't
no small game, you hear?</i>

13:22.389 --> 13:24.188
You know,

13:24.190 --> 13:26.758
it's still enough to tear
you apart this close, asshole.

13:26.760 --> 13:29.594
Yeah, you're right.

13:29.596 --> 13:31.863
But you know you're gonna need
something a damn sight more substantial

13:31.865 --> 13:35.332
- if you really wanna roughhouse with me.
- I got plenty, buddy.

13:35.334 --> 13:38.836
You just try to come up them
fucking stairs again, okay?!

13:38.838 --> 13:41.739
I will blow your fucking head clean off.

13:41.741 --> 13:44.245
<i>I'm getting the police
on the line right now.</i>

14:02.295 --> 14:03.530
<i>Phone's dead.</i>

14:05.431 --> 14:08.234
<i>Looks like I caught
you at a bad time.</i>

14:12.338 --> 14:15.309
I've got a cell phone, asshole!

14:20.579 --> 14:21.915
I know, dipshit.

14:25.251 --> 14:26.219
I'm looking at it.

14:28.320 --> 14:30.388
- Shit.
- <i>( chuckles )</i>

14:30.390 --> 14:33.557
You really ought to keep
this on you at all times,

14:33.559 --> 14:35.460
you know, for emergencies and such.

14:35.462 --> 14:37.361
I'm just saying.

14:37.363 --> 14:38.830
Hell, it don't matter anyway.

14:38.832 --> 14:40.965
The nearest cop is at least
a half hour away from here

14:40.967 --> 14:43.670
and I won't need but a
few minutes of your time.

14:45.771 --> 14:47.772
You sound like you're selling me something.

14:47.774 --> 14:49.974
Maybe I am, maybe I ain't, friend.

14:49.976 --> 14:52.313
Look, here's the situation.

14:54.347 --> 14:56.847
That adorable little moppet you
got up there, she's seen my face.

14:56.849 --> 14:58.883
Hell, if she was a snake,
she would've bit me.

14:58.885 --> 15:01.619
So if I don't put a hole in her head,

15:01.621 --> 15:03.620
and I mean like right quick,

15:03.622 --> 15:05.690
somebody's gonna do the same
thing to me and I can't allow that.

15:05.692 --> 15:08.025
So what I need you to do is send her down

15:08.027 --> 15:10.827
<i>so I can tidy things up
a bit, you understand?</i>

15:10.829 --> 15:13.063
Yeah, you think she can identify you.

15:13.065 --> 15:16.333
Oh, yes, I know she will,

15:16.335 --> 15:18.036
as quick as a frog can lick flies.

15:18.038 --> 15:19.770
But you, on the other hand,

15:19.772 --> 15:21.572
<i>you didn't see fuck all
except a masked gunman.</i>

15:21.574 --> 15:23.941
I could give less than two shits about you.

15:23.943 --> 15:27.378
All I want's the girl. So why
don't you send her on down here,

15:27.380 --> 15:29.984
<i>let me handle my business,
and I'll be gone.</i>

15:38.692 --> 15:40.857
( sighs ) Look, son,

15:40.859 --> 15:44.595
I understand the, uh, unfortunate

15:44.597 --> 15:47.898
and, uh, complex moral dilemma

15:47.900 --> 15:50.735
<i>that you're facing here.
But it's real simple.</i>

15:50.737 --> 15:53.937
The little lady's seen my face.

15:53.939 --> 15:58.009
<i>Now she's got to pay the
price like everybody else.</i>

15:58.011 --> 16:00.780
That's how it works.

16:02.681 --> 16:05.518
As far as you should be
concerned, she's already dead.

16:07.753 --> 16:10.053
Now, the sooner you allow me

16:10.055 --> 16:12.657
to prove that little point to you,

16:12.659 --> 16:13.890
the sooner you can get back

16:13.892 --> 16:16.661
to your perfect little life here.

16:16.663 --> 16:19.900
- ( groans )
- <i>Now, I know you're bleeding up there.</i>

16:22.035 --> 16:23.768
And that does make time a factor,

16:23.770 --> 16:25.470
so here's what you're gonna do...

16:25.472 --> 16:28.840
you're gonna send the girl down to me.

16:28.842 --> 16:31.642
Get yourself down to a
hospital. Get yourself fixed up.

16:31.644 --> 16:33.543
I'm gonna take care of my
business and that'll be that.

16:33.545 --> 16:34.547
What do you say?

16:36.683 --> 16:38.383
<i>Believe me when I tell you, son,</i>

16:38.385 --> 16:40.851
you do not want to fight me on this thing.

16:40.853 --> 16:44.122
This will only devolve
into a battle of wills

16:44.124 --> 16:46.727
and my will is stronger than
anyone you have ever met.

16:49.828 --> 16:51.162
( sighs )

16:51.164 --> 16:52.433
Yeah?

16:54.501 --> 16:57.501
Well, you and me ain't never
been introduced, asshole.

16:57.503 --> 17:00.637
My name's Carter Greene. This is my house.

17:00.639 --> 17:02.809
Now, so long as I'm still breathing,

17:04.877 --> 17:08.078
you ain't gonna harm a
hair on this child's head.

17:08.079 --> 17:10.448
Listen, you just send the
little lady down here right now.

17:10.450 --> 17:12.682
This is not the time to play hero,

17:12.684 --> 17:15.853
and I am the last individual
on God's green earth

17:15.855 --> 17:17.887
that you wanna butt
heads with, you hear me?

17:17.890 --> 17:19.990
Oh, yeah, I hear ya.

17:19.992 --> 17:22.862
I hear ya and you sound real scary.

17:24.563 --> 17:26.762
Fuck you, Farmer Jim!

17:26.765 --> 17:29.800
You're all alone out here on the frontier.

17:29.802 --> 17:31.669
No friends, no family,

17:31.671 --> 17:34.172
<i>no cops, no help at all.</i>

17:34.174 --> 17:36.574
This is the Wild West, son.

17:36.576 --> 17:39.042
The Wild fucking West.

17:39.044 --> 17:42.480
There ain't no gods coming
out here to save your ass.

17:42.482 --> 17:46.217
It's just you and me and a murder of crows

17:46.219 --> 17:48.853
waiting to pick over our dead bones.

17:48.855 --> 17:51.756
<i>So you take a breather.</i>

17:51.758 --> 17:54.491
You let that sink in.

17:54.493 --> 17:58.462
But don't take too long, ya hear?

17:58.464 --> 17:59.696
You don't wanna get too much blood

17:59.698 --> 18:02.168
all over your white trash fineries.

18:09.209 --> 18:10.942
I need your help.

18:10.944 --> 18:13.009
I want you to go in the
bathroom and get a first aid kit.

18:13.011 --> 18:14.647
It's under the sink. Go.

18:28.027 --> 18:30.228
Come to papa.

18:30.230 --> 18:32.096
Okay, set it down.

18:32.098 --> 18:34.701
Open it up. Come here.

18:36.703 --> 18:38.672
You're gonna help me, okay?

18:42.075 --> 18:43.774
Carter: <i>Pour this on.</i>

18:43.776 --> 18:46.847
Okay. ( groans )

18:50.183 --> 18:52.149
( panting, groaning )

18:52.151 --> 18:55.952
- ( screams )
- Get it real hot, okay?

18:55.954 --> 18:58.058
<i>Just hold it on there.</i>

19:03.061 --> 19:05.096
All right, slowly put it down.

19:05.098 --> 19:06.700
Don't look.

19:09.769 --> 19:12.772
- ( Carter screams )
- ( Sade screams )

19:17.976 --> 19:19.213
Carter: More.

19:20.613 --> 19:23.180
More, more, more. Come on.

19:23.182 --> 19:25.486
There.

19:30.623 --> 19:32.826
You're supposed to swallow them.

19:37.629 --> 19:40.631
Not when you hurt as bad as I do.

19:40.633 --> 19:43.768
Go... go in the other room.

19:43.770 --> 19:46.938
In a box there are some light bulbs, okay?

19:46.940 --> 19:48.638
Bring me all of them.

19:48.640 --> 19:52.609
And some water. Bring me some water.

19:52.611 --> 19:54.848
<i>( footsteps creaking )</i>

20:04.656 --> 20:06.760
I said all of them. Go.

20:14.834 --> 20:16.968
And towels, bring me some towels.

20:16.970 --> 20:19.740
The bathroom, go. Go.

20:24.844 --> 20:26.613
Please.

20:39.759 --> 20:41.028
Good.

20:56.142 --> 20:58.045
<i>( glass shatters )</i>

21:13.126 --> 21:15.326
That ain't no farmer.

21:15.328 --> 21:17.694
Now even if we're not here,

21:17.696 --> 21:20.196
- we'll hear him if he tries going up the stairs.
- Cool.

21:20.198 --> 21:22.732
What's the water for?

21:22.734 --> 21:25.038
It's for drinking.

21:27.339 --> 21:28.942
Oh.

21:30.742 --> 21:32.311
Want some?

21:33.713 --> 21:36.916
<i>( creaking )</i>

21:40.986 --> 21:42.822
<i>( clatters )</i>

21:50.163 --> 21:53.297
- So, what's your name?
- Isabelle.

21:53.299 --> 21:56.200
But everyone calls me Bird.
I don't like it, though.

21:56.202 --> 21:57.934
Bird?

21:57.936 --> 22:00.971
How'd you get a colorful name like that?

22:00.973 --> 22:03.007
My dad gave it to me.

22:03.009 --> 22:05.843
My mom said he started
calling me his little bird

22:05.845 --> 22:08.315
when I was real small
'cause I never wanted to eat.

22:09.915 --> 22:11.717
He died, though.

22:13.118 --> 22:14.919
They both did.

22:14.921 --> 22:19.226
- Car crash.
- <i>( clattering )</i>

22:21.159 --> 22:22.995
God, I'm...

22:24.196 --> 22:26.232
( exhales ) I'm sorry.

22:29.434 --> 22:32.903
How'd you get in this mess, anyway?

22:32.905 --> 22:34.939
He shot Roger at the cemetery.

22:34.941 --> 22:37.807
- Roger?
- Aunt Jane's boyfriend.

22:37.809 --> 22:39.943
( exhales )

22:39.945 --> 22:43.213
Jesus. I'm sorry.

22:43.215 --> 22:45.816
You apologize a lot

22:45.818 --> 22:47.953
for someone who didn't do anything wrong.

22:50.188 --> 22:52.056
I know. I... I just meant

22:52.058 --> 22:54.157
you know, it's too bad your uncle's dead.

22:54.159 --> 22:57.060
He wasn't my uncle.

22:57.062 --> 23:00.232
But I should've been nicer to him.

23:18.283 --> 23:20.286
- ( exhales )
- <i>( clattering )</i>

23:44.443 --> 23:46.879
He's a monster.

23:49.248 --> 23:51.981
He's no monster. Hey.

23:51.983 --> 23:54.884
Don't give him the satisfaction.

23:54.886 --> 23:56.487
He's no monster.

23:56.489 --> 23:59.192
Yes, he is.

24:03.061 --> 24:04.428
You're all alone?

24:04.430 --> 24:06.430
This big company just moved in

24:06.432 --> 24:08.566
and this whole valley's a graveyard.

24:08.568 --> 24:12.138
The crops are alive,
but the houses are dead.

24:13.940 --> 24:16.343
There's nobody here but scarecrows.

24:17.577 --> 24:19.112
And you.

24:20.479 --> 24:22.415
And me.

24:26.918 --> 24:29.953
- <i>( ball bounces )</i>
- How many bullets do you have?

24:29.955 --> 24:31.891
Just the one.

24:33.158 --> 24:35.124
That's it?

24:35.126 --> 24:38.162
<i>You don't have any more
packed in a box or something?</i>

24:38.164 --> 24:40.064
I'm afraid not.

24:40.066 --> 24:42.465
Last shell in the house.

24:42.467 --> 24:44.902
Don't worry, though.

24:44.904 --> 24:47.273
He doesn't know that.

24:48.374 --> 24:50.441
Can we go out a window?

24:50.443 --> 24:54.010
No. I mean, I'd never
make it with this leg.

24:54.012 --> 24:55.645
You could climb out on your own.

24:55.647 --> 24:58.449
But then I wouldn't be
there to protect you,

24:58.451 --> 25:00.017
and that's just what he wants.

25:00.019 --> 25:02.553
<i>No, we're stuck here
until help comes</i>

25:02.555 --> 25:04.989
<i>or he leaves.</i>

25:04.991 --> 25:07.892
<i>( clattering )</i>

25:07.894 --> 25:09.095
Thank you.

25:10.596 --> 25:12.195
No, don't mention it, Isabelle.

25:12.197 --> 25:14.533
Just... just doing what's right.

25:16.202 --> 25:17.604
Call me Bird if you want.

25:19.137 --> 25:21.107
I thought you didn't like that name.

25:23.309 --> 25:25.212
Depends on who's using it.

25:28.647 --> 25:31.147
Well, pleased to meet you, Bird.

25:31.149 --> 25:33.853
I'm Carter, in case you missed it.

25:43.428 --> 25:45.194
( sighs )

25:45.196 --> 25:47.064
It's a nice camera you got there.

25:47.066 --> 25:49.935
What, are you taking pictures
of the cemetery or something?

25:51.971 --> 25:55.638
Him. I got a picture of
him without his mask on.

25:55.640 --> 25:58.174
- Does he know that?
- I think so.

25:58.176 --> 26:00.512
Well, that's great. Give me the film.

26:06.719 --> 26:09.586
Sade: <i>Hey, tough guy!</i>

26:09.588 --> 26:11.622
<i>I was wondering.</i>

26:11.624 --> 26:13.159
<i>Let me ask you.</i>

26:16.995 --> 26:19.028
What's with all the boxes, huh?

26:19.030 --> 26:21.533
- <i>( shatters )</i>
- ( coughing )

26:23.301 --> 26:26.670
<i>Fixing to jump ship? Hmm?</i>

26:26.672 --> 26:28.638
<i>I bet you wished you'd
scheduled the big move</i>

26:28.640 --> 26:31.911
a day earlier, huh? ( chuckles )

26:33.279 --> 26:35.278
So, hey, man,

26:35.280 --> 26:38.082
what happened to your family, huh?

26:38.084 --> 26:40.487
What, they up and leave your sorry ass?

26:43.088 --> 26:45.622
<i>Is this a broken
home I'm sitting in?</i>

26:45.624 --> 26:48.124
Come on, badass, talk to me!

26:48.126 --> 26:50.326
Don't be shy!

26:50.328 --> 26:52.565
Shit, you can confide in me.

26:54.599 --> 26:57.267
Whoa, whoa! Lookie here.

26:57.269 --> 26:59.470
Soldier boy.

26:59.472 --> 27:02.205
You're a soldier boy.

27:02.207 --> 27:04.674
Damn good one from the
looks of this photograph.

27:04.676 --> 27:07.144
Look at you, all spit and polish

27:07.146 --> 27:09.413
with your shiny medals
and your pretty ribbons.

27:09.415 --> 27:11.414
<i>Hey, where... where were you?</i>

27:11.416 --> 27:13.083
<i>Huh?</i>

27:13.085 --> 27:14.785
Hey, look, I'm ex-military, too, man.

27:14.787 --> 27:17.520
Black ops, you know, real
jackal shit. Where were you?

27:17.522 --> 27:20.423
Iraq? No, no, no.

27:20.425 --> 27:22.593
Afghanistan.

27:22.595 --> 27:24.260
Hey, Sar. Greene!

27:24.262 --> 27:27.698
Hey, Sar. Greene, as one
ex-military man to another,

27:27.700 --> 27:30.567
I salute you

27:30.569 --> 27:33.440
and thank you for your service. ( chuckles )

27:36.207 --> 27:37.607
Damn.

27:37.609 --> 27:40.109
Nice-looking woman you had there, boy.

27:40.111 --> 27:43.047
Real nice-looking.

27:43.049 --> 27:44.347
<i>Hey, you don't mind
if I get her number</i>

27:44.349 --> 27:45.715
<i>when this is all over, do you?</i>

27:45.717 --> 27:47.483
- Just shut up!
- Hey!

27:47.485 --> 27:50.554
- <i>Shut your fucking mouth!</i>
- ( laughs )

27:50.556 --> 27:52.756
Oh, come on, Sar. Greene!

27:52.758 --> 27:55.328
I'm just fucking with you a little bit.

27:58.230 --> 28:00.064
Ah!

28:00.066 --> 28:01.432
Ain't no need for you to get

28:01.434 --> 28:04.233
all furiously articulate on me.

28:04.235 --> 28:06.737
Hey, uh,

28:06.739 --> 28:09.440
just wanna thank you.

28:09.442 --> 28:12.241
Took the liberty of dipping
into your little reserve.

28:12.243 --> 28:14.478
I've been feeling nice and warm.

28:14.480 --> 28:16.547
<i>I hope you got something up there
to keep the chill away, too.</i>

28:16.549 --> 28:18.682
Oh, and, uh,

28:18.684 --> 28:20.784
all bullshit aside,

28:20.786 --> 28:23.554
just between you and me,

28:23.556 --> 28:25.823
<i>I understand where you're
coming from with all this, man.</i>

28:25.825 --> 28:27.657
I understand. I got a little girl myself.

28:27.659 --> 28:30.259
She ain't but... well,
she can't be no older

28:30.261 --> 28:32.162
than the little lady up there

28:32.164 --> 28:35.432
and she means the world to me.

28:35.434 --> 28:38.201
Uh, nothing I wouldn't
do for that little girl.

28:38.203 --> 28:39.670
I mean, that's why I'm
in this line of work.

28:39.672 --> 28:41.538
You know, I got a family that depends on me

28:41.540 --> 28:44.575
and I can't let one little
loose end with a ponytail

28:44.577 --> 28:46.442
take 'em away from me, can I?

28:46.444 --> 28:48.644
I mean, you can't let her get in the way

28:48.646 --> 28:51.214
of you taking care of your
responsibilities either.

28:51.216 --> 28:54.317
Right? I mean, what's more important,

28:54.319 --> 28:56.487
the life of a stranger or...

28:56.489 --> 28:58.221
or the future of your family?

28:58.223 --> 29:00.490
<i>You feel me?</i>

29:00.492 --> 29:02.459
- Take this...
- <i>I mean, am I right?</i>

29:02.461 --> 29:04.795
- Put it in the back of the toilet.
- In the toilet?

29:04.797 --> 29:06.563
In the... in the tank.

29:06.565 --> 29:08.568
- Put it in the tank.
- Oh, okay.

29:09.801 --> 29:12.201
<i>( footsteps creaking )</i>

29:12.203 --> 29:14.171
Hey, let me ask you this.

29:14.173 --> 29:15.806
You wanna see your son again, right?

29:15.808 --> 29:18.174
<i>I mean, am I right?</i>

29:18.176 --> 29:20.477
Well, you ain't wrong, mister.

29:20.479 --> 29:23.212
But what you think I got to lose, man,

29:23.214 --> 29:24.647
I already lost.

29:24.649 --> 29:28.785
The kid stays with me, all right?

29:28.787 --> 29:31.255
Why don't you just go home
to your own daughter, huh?

29:31.257 --> 29:33.490
No can do, partner.

29:33.492 --> 29:35.826
- ( discordant notes playing )
- ( coughs )

29:35.828 --> 29:38.494
No can do.

29:38.496 --> 29:41.832
Once I sink my teeth into
something, I don't pull 'em out

29:41.834 --> 29:43.733
<i>till the thing is dead.</i>

29:43.735 --> 29:45.935
Yeah, you sure about that, pal?

29:45.937 --> 29:48.305
Now, I wouldn't bet on you lasting too long

29:48.307 --> 29:50.574
- with that buckshot in your gut.
- <i>Aw, shit, man,</i>

29:50.576 --> 29:53.576
by my standards this ain't
nothing but a flesh wound.

29:53.578 --> 29:55.578
Yeah, well, mine's a flesh
wound by anybody's standards,

29:55.580 --> 29:58.548
so we'll just see who drops first.

29:58.550 --> 30:00.651
Well, I got a feeling
that that's gonna be you

30:00.653 --> 30:03.452
once I burn this
motherfucker to the ground.

30:03.454 --> 30:05.189
What you got to say to that?

30:05.191 --> 30:07.657
I'm way ahead of you, asshole.

30:07.659 --> 30:10.493
<i>Now, you know just as well as I do</i>

30:10.495 --> 30:12.663
the kid's got a picture of
you without your mask on.

30:12.665 --> 30:14.698
You see, I got you, man!

30:14.700 --> 30:17.634
<i>Film's in a safe place.
It's in a Ziploc bag</i>

30:17.636 --> 30:19.368
<i>under the fucking water.</i>

30:19.370 --> 30:21.438
<i>You know damn well
there's a decent chance</i>

30:21.440 --> 30:23.440
<i>that film will survive the
fire for the cops to find.</i>

30:23.442 --> 30:24.874
I gotta think, man,

30:24.876 --> 30:27.310
that's well past the
level of acceptable risk

30:27.312 --> 30:30.480
for such a trained
professional as yourself.

30:30.482 --> 30:32.316
You know, your sneering, condescending act

30:32.318 --> 30:34.384
really sucks right about now, soldier boy.

30:34.386 --> 30:36.519
You should've stuck to
the purehearted yokel bit.

30:36.521 --> 30:39.957
- That shit was working for you.
- Whatever you say, chief.

30:39.959 --> 30:43.460
Oh, I'm gonna break you into
a million pieces, motherfucker.

30:43.462 --> 30:46.529
A million tiny fucking pieces.

30:46.531 --> 30:48.464
You wanna play with me?

30:48.466 --> 30:49.569
All right, then.

30:51.270 --> 30:53.473
It's fitting to get ugly up in this bitch.

30:57.609 --> 30:59.643
Dispatch: <i>All quiet on
the western front, kid?</i>

30:59.645 --> 31:01.478
Man: <i>That's right.</i>

31:01.480 --> 31:02.712
Same as yesterday.

31:02.714 --> 31:05.449
Same as every yesterday.

31:05.451 --> 31:07.584
I tell you, I don't know how
this place keeps itself together

31:07.586 --> 31:09.419
between my rounds.

31:09.421 --> 31:10.621
Dispatch: <i>Rookies eat
their grits and like it.</i>

31:10.623 --> 31:12.422
<i>Just swallow and smile, kid.</i>

31:12.424 --> 31:14.258
Hey, I got a question for you.

31:14.260 --> 31:16.727
When are you old dogs
gonna stop calling me "kid"?

31:16.729 --> 31:19.997
<i>Until you earn your
wings. Don't take offense.</i>

31:19.999 --> 31:22.999
<i>That's just how it is
around these parts.</i>

31:23.001 --> 31:25.469
And how do I earn my wings?

31:25.471 --> 31:27.837
<i>Well, you can start by
getting your ass over</i>

31:27.839 --> 31:29.806
<i>to Clem Thatcher's place.</i>

31:29.808 --> 31:32.375
<i>Them teenagers been
messing around on his land.</i>

31:32.377 --> 31:34.246
( sighs ) Again?

31:35.513 --> 31:37.580
Uh...

31:37.582 --> 31:39.418
<i>You see something, kid?</i>

31:41.386 --> 31:44.456
It's probably nothing.
I'll get back to you.

31:46.759 --> 31:47.926
( cuts engine )

31:59.003 --> 32:00.807
( creaking )

32:38.743 --> 32:39.712
( silent )

32:55.860 --> 32:57.696
Bird?

33:00.566 --> 33:03.432
Bird, I need a drink.

33:03.434 --> 33:05.902
More water?

33:05.904 --> 33:06.838
<i>No.</i>

33:08.440 --> 33:10.743
There's some other bottles up in the attic.

33:12.677 --> 33:15.681
Aunt Jane gets angry when she drinks.

33:17.148 --> 33:20.150
Yeah, well, I get angry when I don't drink.

33:20.152 --> 33:22.685
Hey, just...

33:22.687 --> 33:23.790
...go get me a bottle.

33:28.626 --> 33:29.729
( sighs )

34:12.737 --> 34:15.538
- Where did you get that?
- I'm sorry. I'll put it back.

34:15.540 --> 34:17.476
Where did you get that? Put it back.

34:18.577 --> 34:20.612
Put it back now.

34:21.713 --> 34:24.050
<i>( footsteps creaking )</i>

34:29.754 --> 34:32.023
( grunting )

35:09.694 --> 35:11.763
<i>"Mara,</i>

35:13.631 --> 35:16.765
<i>I could never say this to you</i>

35:16.767 --> 35:19.169
<i>face-to-face</i>

35:19.171 --> 35:21.937
even though you told me over and over again

35:21.939 --> 35:24.073
that it wasn't my fault.

35:24.075 --> 35:27.511
Your eyes never hid the truth.

35:27.513 --> 35:29.712
<i>I killed our son.</i>

35:29.714 --> 35:31.117
<i>I let him die.</i>

35:48.033 --> 35:49.598
I want you to know

35:49.600 --> 35:51.667
that you did the right thing leaving me."

35:51.669 --> 35:53.205
You motherfucker.

35:58.776 --> 36:00.743
"I hope one day you find it in your heart

36:00.745 --> 36:02.044
to forgive me.

36:02.046 --> 36:05.314
I'm so sorry I was so weak.

36:05.316 --> 36:07.953
- Carter."
- ( discordant notes playing )

36:16.260 --> 36:19.629
<i>( Sade laughing )</i>

36:19.631 --> 36:21.964
<i>God damn, Sergeant Greene.</i>

36:21.966 --> 36:24.200
That sure is a whole lot of apologies.

36:24.202 --> 36:27.102
Exactly how many kids did you get killed?

36:27.104 --> 36:28.773
<i>( Sade laughing )</i>

36:34.680 --> 36:36.680
Don't look at me.

36:36.682 --> 36:38.584
Don't look at me!

36:40.651 --> 36:43.587
Well, now I know why you
had that cannon so handy.

36:43.589 --> 36:45.988
You packed the place up,

36:45.990 --> 36:48.792
got drunk,

36:48.794 --> 36:50.759
then you stopped and thought about it.

36:50.761 --> 36:54.663
<i>Decided that life wasn't
worth living anymore, was it?</i>

36:54.665 --> 36:55.901
Well, hell...

36:58.236 --> 37:00.370
...don't let this little
fiasco with the kid

37:00.372 --> 37:01.937
ruin your whole afternoon.

37:01.939 --> 37:03.772
By all means, go ahead!

37:03.774 --> 37:05.341
Act like the two of us ain't even here

37:05.343 --> 37:08.713
and blow your goddamn
brains out! ( laughing )

37:11.649 --> 37:14.618
Whoo! Whoo, hoo, hoo!

37:14.620 --> 37:16.720
Oh, but, no, seriously, man,

37:16.722 --> 37:18.721
I know where you're coming from, though.

37:18.723 --> 37:21.156
I do.

37:21.158 --> 37:23.628
<i>Shit, she ain't your kid.</i>

37:25.162 --> 37:26.830
Can't turn back time.

37:26.832 --> 37:27.800
Believe me, I done tried.

37:29.700 --> 37:31.102
<i>But you know I'm
gonna win this thing.</i>

37:32.403 --> 37:35.006
Even Tombstone courage runs out.

37:36.707 --> 37:39.278
You need to go ahead on
and give in to the beast.

37:41.213 --> 37:43.649
Send the little lady down here to me.

37:48.185 --> 37:49.921
Come and get her.

38:01.867 --> 38:03.635
<i>( crow caws )</i>

38:04.903 --> 38:06.339
Hello?

38:08.740 --> 38:10.743
( urinating )

38:17.749 --> 38:19.115
<i>Hey!</i>

38:19.117 --> 38:21.450
<i>You guys wanna order some pizza?</i>

38:21.452 --> 38:23.688
<i>( Sade laughs )</i>

38:27.426 --> 38:28.894
Bird: <i>I'm sorry.</i>

38:31.430 --> 38:33.930
No, don't be sorry. I...

38:33.932 --> 38:36.334
I shouldn't have yelled at you.

38:46.711 --> 38:48.747
What was your son's name?

38:51.783 --> 38:53.019
Sam.

38:54.486 --> 38:56.055
You miss him?

38:58.756 --> 39:00.290
Every day.

39:00.292 --> 39:02.694
I miss my parents, too.

39:06.097 --> 39:08.230
"There ain't no quitting me."

39:08.232 --> 39:10.001
What?

39:11.303 --> 39:12.836
"There ain't no quitting me."

39:12.838 --> 39:15.240
Just something my dad used to say.

39:18.109 --> 39:20.879
It always made me feel safe.

39:24.515 --> 39:27.183
You think I'll see him when I die?

39:27.185 --> 39:30.053
Hey, don't talk like that, okay?

39:30.055 --> 39:32.321
Help will be here soon.

39:32.323 --> 39:36.095
Don't say that, Carter. I'm not stupid.

39:38.530 --> 39:40.229
All right.

39:40.231 --> 39:42.867
Maybe help ain't coming.

39:45.102 --> 39:46.236
( sighs )

39:46.238 --> 39:48.307
But I can promise you this...

39:50.876 --> 39:53.075
I won't let him get you.

39:53.077 --> 39:55.246
<i>You hear me?</i>

39:56.948 --> 39:59.785
I won't let him get you.

40:02.419 --> 40:04.889
You believe me?

40:08.459 --> 40:10.995
Why'd your wife leave?

40:13.865 --> 40:15.430
Me.

40:15.432 --> 40:17.802
This place.

40:20.037 --> 40:23.138
Reminded, uh, her

40:23.140 --> 40:24.776
of him.

40:26.812 --> 40:28.748
I just wish...

40:30.848 --> 40:32.582
( exhales )

40:32.584 --> 40:34.419
<i>just...</i>

40:36.220 --> 40:37.388
<i>wish...</i>

40:43.562 --> 40:45.297
I believe you.

40:48.934 --> 40:51.935
- <i>( gunshot )</i>
- ( Bird gasps )

40:51.937 --> 40:53.535
<i>( Bird's footsteps pounding )</i>

40:53.537 --> 40:56.407
Just keeping you on your toes, buddy.

40:57.876 --> 40:58.975
Here, have another one.

40:58.977 --> 41:01.446
<i>( gunshot echoes )</i>

41:12.390 --> 41:14.357
How y'all doing up there?

41:14.359 --> 41:16.392
Carter: <i>I could ask
you the same question,</i>

41:16.394 --> 41:18.093
<i>you loose sack of shit!</i>

41:18.095 --> 41:20.897
You know, you sound like a sick animal

41:20.899 --> 41:23.533
who's hunting around
for a corner to die in.

41:23.535 --> 41:26.269
<i>You feeling kind of cold?</i>

41:26.271 --> 41:27.937
<i>Kind of weak?</i>

41:27.939 --> 41:29.906
<i>Yeah.</i>

41:29.908 --> 41:32.140
<i>You're going into shock, pal.</i>

41:32.142 --> 41:34.644
<i>Gonna die.</i>

41:34.646 --> 41:37.479
<i>Soon unless you get to a hospital.</i>

41:37.481 --> 41:40.149
Fuck you! I'm fine!

41:40.151 --> 41:42.252
<i>I ain't going nowhere</i>

41:42.254 --> 41:44.453
<i>till that little bitch
is pushing up daisies!</i>

41:44.455 --> 41:48.290
- <i>Period!</i>
- That suits me just fine, mister.

41:48.292 --> 41:50.959
Nothing bleeds forever.

41:50.961 --> 41:52.428
<i>Another few hours,</i>

41:52.430 --> 41:55.031
<i>you'll be lying facedown</i>

41:55.033 --> 41:57.332
<i>in a puddle of your own fluids.</i>

41:57.334 --> 41:59.201
Hey, don't worry, though.

41:59.203 --> 42:01.069
I'll let your daughter know you died

42:01.071 --> 42:03.640
<i>defending the future of your family.</i>

42:03.642 --> 42:06.341
Oh, outstanding, Sergeant Greene.

42:06.343 --> 42:08.144
Out-fucking-standing.

42:08.146 --> 42:10.078
You beat me at my own game.

42:10.080 --> 42:13.549
You're a master of psychological warfare!

42:13.551 --> 42:14.917
Next thing you know,

42:14.919 --> 42:16.919
you'll have me tidying up the place

42:16.921 --> 42:19.221
and giving you a blowjob on the way out.

42:19.223 --> 42:21.256
<i>Brilliant!</i>

42:21.258 --> 42:22.491
<i>( camera shutter clicks )</i>

42:22.493 --> 42:24.593
- Sorry.
- <i>What are you doing?</i>

42:24.595 --> 42:27.398
No film in that camera.

42:29.234 --> 42:31.301
Yeah, it just makes me feel safe.

42:31.303 --> 42:32.538
It's stupid, I know.

42:35.073 --> 42:37.443
We all got our ways of dealing with stuff.

42:48.019 --> 42:50.218
What? What is it?

42:50.220 --> 42:51.520
<i>Shh.</i>

42:51.522 --> 42:54.357
Just reminds me...

42:54.359 --> 42:56.158
we got a problem.

42:56.160 --> 42:58.227
How big?

42:58.229 --> 43:00.330
It's big.

43:00.332 --> 43:02.732
There's a generator in the basement

43:02.734 --> 43:04.334
that runs the whole power, you see?

43:04.336 --> 43:06.171
I haven't filled it up in days.

43:07.472 --> 43:09.504
It's running on fumes.

43:09.506 --> 43:12.008
I don't understand.

43:12.010 --> 43:13.977
It'll be night soon, Bird.

43:13.979 --> 43:16.345
Without any power, the whole
house will be pitch-black.

43:16.347 --> 43:18.046
<i>There's no way I can keep him</i>

43:18.048 --> 43:19.582
from trying something in the dark.

43:19.584 --> 43:21.750
Not with one shot.

43:21.752 --> 43:23.521
What does that mean?

43:26.256 --> 43:28.390
It means I gotta get you out of here

43:28.392 --> 43:30.727
while it's still light out.

43:30.729 --> 43:33.363
But your leg.

43:33.365 --> 43:36.332
I'm not going with you.

43:36.334 --> 43:39.067
I'm gonna help you climb out a
window so you can run for help.

43:39.069 --> 43:41.537
- But you said that's what he wants!
- I know what I said, Bird,

43:41.539 --> 43:43.006
but things are different now, okay?

43:43.008 --> 43:44.774
You gotta trust me on this.

43:44.776 --> 43:47.576
This is your best chance.

43:47.578 --> 43:49.981
<i>Okay?</i>

43:59.024 --> 44:00.960
Oh, fuck.

44:08.265 --> 44:10.165
Hey, is the, uh,

44:10.167 --> 44:12.734
shooting range on Red
Pepper open for the fall yet?

44:12.736 --> 44:15.370
Dispatch: <i>What's that, kid?</i>

44:15.372 --> 44:17.540
The shooting range on Red Pepper,

44:17.542 --> 44:19.207
is it open now?

44:19.209 --> 44:21.310
<i>Nope. Why?</i>

44:21.312 --> 44:23.712
I... I'm not sure, I, uh...

44:23.714 --> 44:26.452
I'm at the cemetery and I heard...

44:28.385 --> 44:30.621
<i>What's that? What did you hear, kid?</i>

44:32.189 --> 44:34.256
<i>Kid?</i>

44:34.258 --> 44:37.192
Nothing. Uh...

44:37.194 --> 44:39.529
I'm gonna look into something.
I'll get back to you.

44:39.531 --> 44:42.201
And stop calling me "kid."

44:43.834 --> 44:45.670
( engine starts )

44:59.584 --> 45:01.183
All right, let's go.

45:01.185 --> 45:02.819
What if he realizes you aren't guarding

45:02.821 --> 45:04.453
the stairs anymore?

45:04.455 --> 45:06.288
We got the broken glass.
We'll hear him. Come on.

45:06.290 --> 45:08.323
Now, I want you to climb
down on this roof, right?

45:08.325 --> 45:09.758
There's a crate. Jump down on it.

45:09.760 --> 45:12.261
Run like hell, all right?

45:12.263 --> 45:14.663
Hey, hey. Even if he hears you,

45:14.665 --> 45:17.366
you'll be a little speck on the
horizon by the time he gets outside.

45:17.368 --> 45:19.569
- I don't wanna do this.
- Neither do I, Bird,

45:19.571 --> 45:21.870
but we have to. We don't have a choice.

45:21.872 --> 45:24.475
<i>( floorboards creaking )</i>

45:44.863 --> 45:47.363
- Come on. Give me the camera.
- No.

45:47.365 --> 45:48.897
Come on, I'll take good care of it.

45:48.899 --> 45:51.369
Don't you trust me? Come on.

45:52.736 --> 45:54.439
Bird, I...

45:56.207 --> 45:58.510
Okay, keep the camera. Come on. Go.

46:00.178 --> 46:01.743
That's it.

46:01.745 --> 46:03.548
Stay low.

46:05.883 --> 46:07.385
